New Records: Zack Wheeler earned his 100th career victory.
Key Match Events: Zack Wheeler pitched seven shutout innings.
Edmundo Sosa homered and doubled, driving in two runs.
Trea Turner hit a home run.
Michael Harris II made a highlight-reel catch robbing Austin Hays of a home run.
Jeff Hoffman struck out two in a scoreless eighth inning.
Carlos Estévez completed the shutout with his 23rd save.
Post-Match Reflections: Zack Wheeler expressed pride in his 100th victory, emphasizing hard work and belief in himself and his teams.
Phillies manager Rob Thomson praised Wheeler's performance.
Edmundo Sosa felt good contributing early with his home run.
Michael Harris II described his catch as 'pretty cool'.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Phillies increased their lead over the Braves in the division to six games.
The game had a sellout crowd of 42,730.
Phillies reinstated left-handed reliever José Alvarado from the restricted list after the game.
